    "art_style": "PROJECT: Latin Reader Series\n\nART STYLE:\nSimple storybook art with clean shapes, light shading, and bright flat colors; gentle and consistent visual tone\n\nCHARACTER DESIGN:\n- Dragon: a red dragon with four legs and two wings. \n\nENVIRONMENT:\n- Background: low complexity; focus on characters and key actions, no visual clutter\n\nCOMPOSITION:\n- Layout: center or slightly lower center framing\n- Camera angle: mostly eye-level or slightly above; keep perspective simple\n- Focus: clear storytelling pose or action per scene, easy for a child to interpret\n- Color palette: cobalt blue accents, warm browns, and soft yellows; avoid dark or saturated tones\n\nTECHNICAL:\n- Aspect ratio: square (1:1) or 4:3 portrait — keep consistent within book\n- Resolution: 512x512 or 640x480 for compact files (low detail, small size)\n- Style consistency: maintain same colors, proportions, and visual tone across all images\n- Output format: PNG or WebP for quality at small file sizes\n\nLAYOUT NOTES:\n- Page flow: each image corresponds to one or two sentences of Latin; keep visual action easy to map to text\n\nAI INSTRUCTIONS:\nKeep visuals simple, warm, and readable for children. Avoid text, labels, or complex shadows. Focus on consistent characters and simple emotions. Each image should clearly illustrate the moment described in the Latin text.\n",
